This paper deals with kernel approximation, a common technique in machine learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses data-dependent sampling methods, which can be considered a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The use of scoring rules and optimization techniques in the paper suggests a connection to the field of data science (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the application of the proposed method to image analysis, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses Canonical Correlation Analysis, which is a statistical technique and falls under the category of cs.SI (Statistics).
